==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharmacy
<hw>Phar"ma*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fermacie</ets>, OF. <ets>farmacie</ets>, <ets>pharmacie</ets>, F.
<ets>pharmacie</ets>, Gr. <grk>farmakei`a</grk>, fr.
<grk>farmakey`ein</grk> to administer or use medicines, fr.
<grk>fa`rmakon</grk> medicine.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art or
practice of preparing and preserving drugs, and of compounding and
dispensing medicines according to prescriptions of physicians; the
occupation of an apothecary or a pharmaceutical chemist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where medicines are compounded; a drug
store; an apothecary's shop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharo</ent>⟦br⟧
